Query Profiler is available only in Ultimate version of SQLyog.
 
Click here to buy SQLyog Ultimate
 
Query Profiler Features:
  • helps you identify problem SQL
  • helps you fine-tune SQL
  • helps you create the right indexes
  • analyzes queries and helps you optimize them
  • reports the exact time spent in each step of query execution
  • helps you write better SQL
  • identifies whether indexes are being used effectively
  • helps you improve overall response time of your application

Welcome to Import External Data Wizard!

This wizard will guide you through the steps to Import External Data and also help you in Scheduling the importing process.
A job file stores the configuration of this task. You can use the job file to run this task again in the future.
You can specify a valid SQL WHERE clause for the table. Only those rows that fulfill the WHERE clause will be imported. (Note: Don't include WHERE in the clause)

To correctly import meta-data like Foreign Keys from an Access database you will require to give permissions on Access system tables. (make sure you have saved the database in .mdb format as User-Level Security features are not available for databases in new file formats like .accdb, .accde, .accdc, .accdr).

The underlying database seems to be using Text File Driver to import. The limitations of the driver are :
1) Tables are limited to a maximum of 255 fields. 2) Field names are limited to 64 characters and field widths are limited to 32,766 characters. 3) Records are limited to 65,000 bytes.
